            "new_string": "3. **Tailwind JIT: are all utility classes pre-generated?** If the target Tailwind class (`p-8`) wasn't in the original build, it may not exist in the stylesheet. Tailwind JIT generates classes on demand at build time, not runtime. If the class doesn't exist, the swap has no effect. Mitigation: for Tailwind apps using JIT, we may need a fallback to CSS `!important` with the computed value. Detection: check if the swapped class actually applies styles via `getComputedStyle` after the swap.\n\n---\n\n## 14. Complete UX Flow — Every State, Event, and Memory Snapshot\n\nThis section traces every user-visible moment from server startup through editing and teardown. Each phase documents: what the user sees, what cursor state is, which events fire, what changes in memory, and what changes in the DOM.\n\n### Phase 1: Server Startup\n\n**User action:** Runs `cortex visual-editor --target 3000` in terminal.\n\n**What happens (server-side):**\n\n1. `startServer({ targetPort: 3000 })` called (`server.ts:461`)\n2. Checks PID file at `.cortex/sidecar.pid` — rejects if another sidecar is alive\n3. `createApp()` generates:\n   - `sessionId` = `randomUUID()` (e.g., `\"a1b2c3d4-...\"`)\n   - `startedAt` = `Date.now()`\n4. Reads `shell.html` from `dist/client/` (or `src/client/` in dev)\n5. Reads all `.js` files from `dist/client/`, replaces template variables:\n   - `__SESSION_ID__` → the generated UUID\n   - `__SIDECAR_ORIGIN__` → `\"http://localhost:3100\"`\n6. Caches script contents in `clientScriptCache` Map\n7. Sets up Express routes:\n   - `/__zerofog/api/*` — REST API (health, status, diff, shutdown)\n   - `/__zerofog/shell` — serves shell HTML\n   - `/__zerofog/client/:script` — serves cached JS files\n   - Sec-Fetch-Dest redirect middleware\n   - Reverse proxy to `http://127.0.0.1:3000`\n8. Attaches WebSocket upgrade handler (editor WS on `/__zerofog`, proxy WS otherwise)\n9. Server listens on port 3100\n10. Writes PID to `.cortex/sidecar.pid`\n\n**Server memory after startup:**\n\n```\nsessionId: \"a1b2c3d4-...\"\nstartedAt: 1709312340000\nclientScriptCache: Map {\n  \"inspector.js\" → \"<full script with SESSION_ID and SIDECAR_ORIGIN baked in>\",\n  \"nav-blocker.js\" → \"...\",\n  \"panel.js\" → \"...\"\n}\nshellHtml: \"<full HTML string>\"\neditorWss: WebSocketServer (no connections yet)\n```\n\n**What user sees:** Terminal output showing sidecar started on port 3100.\n\n---\n\n### Phase 2: Page Load — Browser Navigation\n\n**User action:** Opens `http://localhost:3100/dashboard` in browser.\n\n**What happens — request chain:**\n\n```\nBrowser → GET /dashboard\n  → Sec-Fetch-Dest: \"document\" detected\n  → 302 Redirect to /__zerofog/shell?path=%2Fdashboard\n\nBrowser → GET /__zerofog/shell?path=%2Fdashboard\n  → Returns shell.html (the outer frame)\n```\n\n**Shell HTML renders:**\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┬──────────┐\n│                                             │          │\n│  <iframe class=\"shell-viewport\">            │ #panel-  │\n│    src=\"/dashboard\"                         │  mount   │\n│    sandbox=\"allow-same-origin               │ (320px)  │\n│             allow-scripts                   │          │\n│             allow-forms                     │ empty    │\n│             allow-modals                    │ for now  │\n│             allow-popups                    │          │\n│             allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\" │          │\n│                                             │          │\n│  (flex: 1 — fills remaining width)          │          │\n│                                             │          │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────┴──────────┘\n```\n\n**Shell script executes:**\n1. Reads `path` from URL params → `\"/dashboard\"`\n2. Validates: starts with `/`, not `//` → OK\n3. Sets `iframe.src = \"/dashboard\"`\n\n**Iframe loads `/dashboard` through the proxy:**\n\n```\niframe → GET /dashboard\n  → Sec-Fetch-Dest: \"iframe\" (NOT \"document\") — no redirect\n  → Proxy forwards to http://127.0.0.1:3000/dashboard\n  → Target dev server responds with HTML\n  → Proxy intercepts HTML response:\n    a. Decompresses (gzip/br/deflate) if needed\n    b. Rewrites Content-Security-Policy:\n       - Removes frame-ancestors (allows iframing)\n       - Ensures script-src includes 'self' (allows injected scripts)\n    c. Strips X-Frame-Options header\n    d. Calls injectScripts(html):\n       - Checks for <!-- __zerofog_injected__ --> marker (idempotent)\n       - Inserts before last </body>:\n         <script src=\"/__zerofog/client/inspector.js\"></script>\n         <script src=\"/__zerofog/client/nav-blocker.js\"></script>\n    e. Sets Content-Length, sends response\n```\n\n**Panel script loads:** `<script src=\"/__zerofog/client/panel.js\">` in shell (currently placeholder `export {}`)\n\n**What user sees:** The app renders normally inside the left iframe. The right panel area (320px) is empty/grey. No visual editing UI yet.\n\n**Cursor:** Default browser cursor.\n\n---\n\n### Phase 3: Inspector Initialization (Inside Iframe)\n\n**Trigger:** Browser parses the injected `<script src=\"/__zerofog/client/inspector.js\">`.\n\n**Execution sequence:**\n\n1. **Template variables already resolved** (server did this at startup):\n   ```javascript\n   var SESSION_ID = 'a1b2c3d4-...';        // real UUID\n   var SIDECAR_ORIGIN = 'http://localhost:3100';  // real origin\n   ```\n\n2. **Constants defined:**\n   ```javascript\n   var MAX_CHAIN_DEPTH = 20;\n   var MAX_ANCESTOR_DEPTH = 50;\n   var MAX_ELEMENT_MAP_SIZE = 50;\n   var MSG_VERSION = 1;\n   ```\n\n3. **Pure functions defined at module scope** (not in IIFE — available for testing):\n   - `getComponentName(fiber)` — extracts displayName/name from fiber.type\n   - `findReactFiberKeys(element)` — scans Object.keys for `__reactFiber$*`\n   - `walkComponentChain(fiber)` — traverses owner chain (React 18 or 19 strategy)\n   - `isFiberAncestor(child, ancestor)` — checks fiber.return chain for stateNode match\n   - `resolveSource(element)` — builds `{ testId, componentChain, hasClientFiber, element }`\n   - `classifyElement(chain, tag)` — returns element category string\n   - `postToParent(type, payload)` — sends postMessage to parent with sessionId\n   - `isValidInbound(e)` — validates inbound messages (origin + sessionId)\n\n4. **Browser context check passes:** `typeof window !== 'undefined' && typeof document !== 'undefined'`\n\n5. **Namespace init:** `window.__ZEROFOG__ = window.__ZEROFOG__ || {}`\n\n6. **IIFE executes — `activate()` called:**\n\n   a. `deactivate()` called first (idempotent cleanup — no-ops on first run)\n\n   b. Creates three overlay elements (appended to `document.body`):\n\n   | Element | ID | Border | Background | Purpose |\n   |---------|-----|--------|-----------|---------|\n   | `overlay` | `__zerofog_inspector_overlay__` | 2px solid #3b82f6 (blue) | rgba(59,130,246,0.08) | Hover highlight |\n   | `selectedOverlay` | `__zerofog_inspector_selected__` | 2px solid #22c55e (green) | rgba(34,197,94,0.1) | Selection highlight |\n   | `labelEl` | `__zerofog_inspector_label__` | none | #18181b (dark bg) | Component name label |\n\n   All three: `position:fixed; pointer-events:none; z-index:2147483647; display:none`\n   All three: `data-zerofog-ui=\"true\"` attribute (for self-exclusion from selection)\n\n   c. `active = true`, `window.__ZEROFOG__.inspectorActive = true`\n\n   d. **Event listeners registered:**\n\n   | Event | Phase | Handler | Purpose |\n   |-------|-------|---------|---------|\n   | `mouseover` | Capture | `handleHover` | Blue overlay positioning |\n   | `pointerdown` | Capture | `handlePointerDown` | Prevent app click in select mode |\n   | `click` | Capture | `handleClick` | Element selection |\n   | `keydown` | Capture | `handleKeyDown` | Escape to deactivate |\n   | `message` | Bubble (window) | `handleMessage` | Cross-frame communication |\n\n   e. `postToParent('zerofog:ready', null)` — tells shell the inspector is ready\n\n**DOM after initialization:**\n\n```html\n<!-- Inside iframe's <body> -->\n<div id=\"__zerofog_inspector_overlay__\" data-zerofog-ui=\"true\"\n     style=\"position:fixed;pointer-events:none;z-index:2147483647;\n            border:2px solid #3b82f6;background:rgba(59,130,246,0.08);\n            transition:all 0.1s ease;display:none;\">\n</div>\n<div id=\"__zerofog_inspector_selected__\" data-zerofog-ui=\"true\"\n     style=\"position:fixed;pointer-events:none;z-index:2147483647;\n            border:2px solid #22c55e;background:rgba(34,197,94,0.1);\n            transition:all 0.1s ease;display:none;\">\n</div>\n<div id=\"__zerofog_inspector_label__\" data-zerofog-ui=\"true\"\n     style=\"position:fixed;pointer-events:none;z-index:2147483647;\n            background:#18181b;color:#fff;font-size:11px;font-family:monospace;\n            padding:2px 6px;border-radius:3px;display:none;white-space:nowrap;\">\n</div>\n```\n\n**JavaScript memory after initialization:**\n\n```javascript\n// IIFE closure scope:\nactive = true\nselectMode = false            // waiting for panel to send enter-select\nselectionId = 0\nelementMap = {}               // Object.create(null), empty\nlastHoverTarget = null\nhoverRafPending = false\noverlay = <div#__zerofog_inspector_overlay__>\nselectedOverlay = <div#__zerofog_inspector_selected__>\nlabelEl = <div#__zerofog_inspector_label__>\n\n// Message dispatch table:\nmessageHandlers = {\n  'inspector:enter-select': fn,  // sets selectMode = true\n  'inspector:exit-select': fn,   // sets selectMode = false\n  // Phase 4b will add:\n  // 'zerofog:preview': fn,      // calls applyOverride\n  // 'zerofog:revert': fn,       // calls removeOverride\n}\n\n// Override engine (Phase 4b — not yet present in current code):\noverrideRules = {}            // Object.create(null)\noverrideRecords = {}          // Object.create(null) — NEW in this spec\n\n// Global namespace:\nwindow.__ZEROFOG__ = {\n  activateInspector: fn,\n  deactivateInspector: fn,\n  selected: null,\n  inspectorActive: true,\n  selectMode: false,\n  elementMap: {}              // reference to same object\n}\n```\n\n**What user sees:** No visual change — all overlays are `display:none`. The app looks exactly as it would without the editor.\n\n**Cursor:** Default browser cursor.\n\n---\n\n### Phase 4: Enter Select Mode\n\n**Trigger:** Panel sends postMessage to iframe (when user clicks \"Select Element\" in panel, or panel auto-enters on load).\n\n**Message sent (shell → iframe):**\n\n```javascript\niframe.contentWindow.postMessage({\n  type: 'inspector:enter-select',\n  sessionId: 'a1b2c3d4-...',\n  version: 1,\n  payload: undefined\n}, 'http://localhost:3100');\n```\n\n**Inspector processing:**\n\n1. `window 'message'` event fires\n2. `handleMessage(e)` called\n3. `isValidInbound(e)` validates:\n   - `e.origin === 'http://localhost:3100'` ✓\n   - `e.data` is object ✓\n   - `e.data` has own property `sessionId` ✓ (uses `Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty.call`)\n   - `e.data.sessionId === SESSION_ID` ✓\n4. Dispatch: `messageHandlers['inspector:enter-select'](undefined)`\n5. `selectMode = true`\n6. `window.__ZEROFOG__.selectMode = true`\n\n**Memory change:**\n\n```\nselectMode: false → true\nwindow.__ZEROFOG__.selectMode: false → true\n```\n\n**What user sees:** Still no visual change. But now mouse interactions will trigger overlays.\n\n**Cursor:** Default cursor (the overlays have `pointer-events:none`).\n\n---\n\n### Phase 5: Hover — Mouse Movement Over Elements\n\n**User action:** Moves mouse over a `<Card>` component in the app.\n\n**Event chain:**\n\n1. `mouseover` fires (capture phase) on the hovered `<div>` element\n2. `handleHover(e)` called\n3. **Guard checks:**\n   - `active` is true ✓\n   - `e.target` is not overlay/selectedOverlay/labelEl ✓\n   - `e.target.closest('[data-zerofog-ui=\"true\"]')` returns null ✓ (not a zerofog UI element)\n   - `e.target !== lastHoverTarget` ✓ (new element)\n4. `lastHoverTarget = e.target` (stores DOM reference)\n5. `hoverRafPending` is false → schedules `requestAnimationFrame`:\n   - `hoverRafPending = true`\n   - RAF callback:\n     - `hoverRafPending = false`\n     - Guards: `active && lastHoverTarget && document.contains(lastHoverTarget)` ✓\n     - Calls `updateHoverOverlay(lastHoverTarget)`\n\n**`updateHoverOverlay` execution:**\n\n1. `target.getBoundingClientRect()` → `{ top: 200, left: 100, width: 400, height: 120 }`\n2. `positionOverlay(overlay, rect)`:\n   ```\n   overlay.style.top = '200px'\n   overlay.style.left = '100px'\n   overlay.style.width = '400px'\n   overlay.style.height = '120px'\n   overlay.style.display = 'block'    // becomes visible!\n   ```\n3. `resolveSource(target)`:\n   - Checks `target.getAttribute('data-testid')` → `\"dashboard-card\"`\n   - `findReactFiberKeys(target)` → `['__reactFiber$abc123']`\n   - Gets fiber: `target['__reactFiber$abc123']`\n   - `walkComponentChain(fiber)`:\n     - Checks `hasOwnProperty(fiber, '_debugOwner')` → true (React 18)\n     - Walks chain: `Card` → `DashboardPage` → `AppShell`\n     - Returns `['Card', 'DashboardPage', 'AppShell']`\n   - Portal check: testId is own → skip\n   - Returns:\n     ```javascript\n     {\n       testId: 'dashboard-card',\n       componentChain: ['Card', 'DashboardPage', 'AppShell'],\n       hasClientFiber: true,\n       element: {\n         tag: 'DIV',\n         classes: ['mantine-Card-root', 'm_bebf4c1'],\n         text: 'Revenue Overview...',\n         bounds: { top: 200, left: 100, width: 400, height: 120 }\n       }\n     }\n     ```\n4. Formats label: `\"Card <div> [dashboard-card]\"`\n5. Positions label:\n   ```\n   labelEl.textContent = 'Card <div> [dashboard-card]'\n   labelEl.style.top = '178px'   // Math.max(0, 200 - 22)\n   labelEl.style.left = '100px'\n   labelEl.style.display = 'block'\n   ```\n\n**What user sees:**\n\n```\n         Card <div> [dashboard-card]     ← dark label, monospace\n┌──────────────────────────────────────┐\n│  ░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░  │ ← blue translucent overlay\n│  ░░  Revenue Overview            ░░  │   (2px blue border +\n│  ░░  $42,150 this month          ░░  │    8% opacity blue fill)\n│  ░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░  │\n└──────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n**Cursor:** Default cursor (overlay has `pointer-events:none`, so the browser shows whatever cursor the underlying element has). The app's hover effects (e.g., card hover states) still work because the overlay doesn't intercept pointer events.\n\n**Memory after hover:**\n\n```\nlastHoverTarget = <div.mantine-Card-root>   // direct DOM reference\nhoverRafPending = false\n```\n\n**Hover on rapid mouse movement:**\n- If user moves mouse fast across many elements, `handleHover` fires for each\n- RAF throttling ensures only one overlay update per frame (16ms)\n- `lastHoverTarget` updates immediately, but overlay position updates on next frame\n- Same element → `target === lastHoverTarget` check exits early (no RAF scheduled)\n\n---\n\n### Phase 6: Click — Element Selection\n\n**User action:** Clicks on the hovered Card element.\n\n**Event chain (two events, both capture phase):**\n\n**Event 1: `pointerdown`**\n\n1. `handlePointerDown(e)` called\n2. `active && selectMode` → both true ✓\n3. `e.stopPropagation()` — prevents the app from seeing the pointerdown\n4. `e.preventDefault()` — prevents focus/text selection\n\n**Event 2: `click`**\n\n1. `handleClick(e)` called\n2. `active && selectMode` → both true ✓\n3. `e.stopPropagation()` — prevents the app's click handler\n4. `e.preventDefault()` — prevents navigation/form submission\n\n5. **Guard checks:** target is not overlay/label/zerofog-ui ✓\n\n6. **Position green selection overlay:**\n   ```javascript\n   var rect = target.getBoundingClientRect();\n   positionOverlay(selectedOverlay, rect);\n   // selectedOverlay now visible with green border\n   ```\n\n7. **Resolve source info:**\n   ```javascript\n   var info = resolveSource(target);\n   // Same as hover: { testId: 'dashboard-card', componentChain: [...], ... }\n   ```\n\n8. **Get computed styles:**\n   ```javascript\n   var computed = window.getComputedStyle(target);\n   ```\n\n9. **Classify element:**\n   ```javascript\n   var elementType = classifyElement(['Card', 'DashboardPage', 'AppShell'], 'DIV');\n   // 'Card' matches container list → returns 'container'\n   ```\n\n10. **Store element reference:**\n    ```javascript\n    selectionId++;  // 0 → 1\n    elementMap[1] = target;  // direct DOM reference\n\n    // Eviction check: Object.keys(elementMap).length > 50? No → skip\n    ```\n\n11. **Build selection object:**\n    ```javascript\n    var selection = {\n      id: 1,\n      timestamp: 1709312345678,\n      testId: 'dashboard-card',\n      componentChain: ['Card', 'DashboardPage', 'AppShell'],\n      hasClientFiber: true,\n      elementType: 'container',\n      element: {\n        tag: 'DIV',\n        classes: ['mantine-Card-root', 'm_bebf4c1'],\n        text: 'Revenue Overview...',\n        bounds: { top: 200, left: 100, width: 400, height: 120 }\n      },\n      styles: {\n        color: 'rgb(0, 0, 0)',\n        background: 'rgba(0, 0, 0, 0) none repeat ...',\n        fontSize: '16px',\n        padding: '16px',\n        margin: '0px',\n        display: 'flex',\n        gap: '8px',\n        borderRadius: '8px',\n        fontWeight: '400',\n        fontFamily: '-apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, ...'\n      }\n    };\n    ```\n\n12. **Publish selection:**\n    ```javascript\n    window.__ZEROFOG__.selected = selection;\n\n    // Local event (for toolbar IIFE, if injected):\n    document.dispatchEvent(new CustomEvent('zerofog:selected', { detail: selection }));\n\n    // Cross-frame (to panel in shell):\n    postToParent('zerofog:selected', selection);\n    // → window.parent.postMessage({ type: 'zerofog:selected', sessionId, version: 1, payload: selection }, SIDECAR_ORIGIN)\n    ```\n\n**What user sees:**\n\n```\n         Card <div> [dashboard-card]     ← label still visible\n┌──────────────────────────────────────┐\n│  ░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░  │ ← GREEN overlay now\n│  ░░  Revenue Overview            ░░  │   (2px green border +\n│  ░░  $42,150 this month          ░░  │    10% opacity green fill)\n│  ░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░  │\n└──────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\nBlue hover overlay is still active underneath (follows mouse). Green overlay stays pinned to the selected element.\n\n**Cursor:** Default cursor (no change — overlay is pointer-events:none).\n\n**Memory after click:**\n\n```javascript\nselectionId = 1\nelementMap = { 1: <div.mantine-Card-root> }  // DOM reference stored\nwindow.__ZEROFOG__.selected = { id: 1, ... }  // full selection object\n```\n\n---\n\n### Phase 7: Origin Detection + Panel Display\n\n**Trigger:** Shell receives `zerofog:selected` postMessage from iframe.\n\n**Critical detail: where does `detectStyleOrigin` run?**\n\n`detectStyleOrigin` needs access to the DOM element's React fiber (`__reactFiber$*` property) and the element's `className`. These only exist inside the iframe. The panel is in the shell (different document context).\n\n**Two possible flows (architecture decision):**\n\n**Option A — Inspector runs origin detection at selection time:**\n\nThe inspector calls `detectStyleOrigin` for each editable property and includes the results in the selection payload:\n\n```javascript\n// Added to handleClick, after building selection:\nvar editableProps = ['padding', 'margin', 'gap', 'border-radius'];\nvar origins = {};\nfor (var pi = 0; pi < editableProps.length; pi++) {\n  origins[editableProps[pi]] = detectStyleOrigin(target, editableProps[pi]);\n}\nselection.origins = origins;\n```\n\nSelection payload sent to panel now includes:\n\n```javascript\nselection.origins = {\n  padding: { origin: 'mantine-prop', prop: 'p', value: 'md', component: 'Card' },\n  margin: { origin: 'unknown' },\n  gap: { origin: 'mantine-prop', prop: 'gap', value: 8, component: 'Card' },\n  'border-radius': { origin: 'mantine-prop', prop: 'radius', value: 'md', component: 'Card' }\n}\n```\n\n**Option B — Panel sends request, inspector responds:**\n\nPanel sends `zerofog:detect-origin` message, inspector responds with origins. More messages but decouples selection from detection.\n\n**Recommendation:** Option A. One message, no round-trip latency. Origin detection is fast (bounded by MAX_DEPTH=20 fiber walks). Including it in the selection payload keeps the protocol simple.\n\n**Panel receives selection + origins:**\n\n1. Reads `selection.elementType` → `'container'`\n2. Looks up editable categories for containers: `['padding', 'margin', 'gap', 'border-radius']`\n3. For each category, reads `selection.origins[category]` to know the rendering strategy\n4. For each category, reads `selection.styles[category]` to know the current value\n5. Resolves current pixel values to design tokens via `reverseTokenLookup`:\n   - `padding: '16px'` → token map lookup → `'md'`\n   - `gap: '8px'` → token map lookup → `'xs'`\n   - `borderRadius: '8px'` → token map lookup → `'md'`\n\n**Panel renders token editing UI:**\n\n```\n┌──────────────────────────────────────┬──────────────────────┐\n│                                      │  TOKEN TOOLBAR       │\n│   App renders here in iframe...      │                      │\n│                                      │  Padding    ▸ mantine│\n│   ┌────────────────────────────┐     │  [xs][sm][●md][lg][xl]\n│   │  ░░ Revenue Overview ░░░░  │     │                      │\n│   │  ░░ (green selection)  ░░  │     │  Margin              │\n│   └────────────────────────────┘     │  [xs][sm][md][lg][xl]│\n│                                      │                      │\n│                                      │  Gap         ▸ mantine\n│                                      │  [xs][●sm][md][lg][xl]\n│                                      │                      │\n│                                      │  Radius      ▸ mantine\n│                                      │  [xs][sm][●md][lg][xl]\n│                                      │                      │\n│                                      │  [    Done    ]      │\n└──────────────────────────────────────┴──────────────────────┘\n```\n\n**Token button states:**\n- `●md` = active (current value) — dark background (`#27272a`), white text, 1px border\n- `sm`, `lg`, etc. = inactive — transparent background, grey text (`#a1a1aa`)\n- Origin indicator: \"▸ mantine\" shown next to category label (new in this spec)\n\n**Panel memory:**\n\n```javascript\n// Panel state (in shell context):\ncurrentSelection = { id: 1, elementType: 'container', origins: {...}, styles: {...}, ... }\npendingChanges = {}           // nothing changed yet\n```\n\n**What user sees:** The panel populates with token buttons for the selected element's editable properties. Current values are highlighted. Origin labels tell the user which framework owns each property.\n\n---\n\n### Phase 8: Token Hover — Live Preview\n\n**User action:** Hovers mouse over the \"lg\" button in the Padding row.\n\n**Panel processing:**\n\n1. Token button's `onmouseover` fires\n2. Panel determines `cssValue` based on origin:\n   - Origin is `mantine-prop` → resolves to `'var(--mantine-spacing-lg)'`\n   - (If origin were `tailwind` → would resolve to `'p-8'`)\n   - (If origin were `css-module` → would resolve to `'40px'`)\n\n3. Panel sends `zerofog:preview` postMessage to iframe:\n   ```javascript\n   iframe.contentWindow.postMessage({\n     type: 'zerofog:preview',\n     sessionId: 'a1b2c3d4-...',\n     version: 1,\n     payload: {\n       selectionId: 1,\n       cssProperty: 'padding',\n       cssValue: 'var(--mantine-spacing-lg)',\n       origin: { origin: 'mantine-prop', prop: 'p', value: 'md', component: 'Card' }\n     }\n   }, 'http://localhost:3100');\n   ```\n\n**Inspector processing:**\n\n1. `handleMessage` → `isValidInbound` ✓ → dispatches to `messageHandlers['zerofog:preview']`\n2. Calls `applyOverride(1, 'padding', 'var(--mantine-spacing-lg)', origin)`\n3. **Validation gates:**\n   - `selId` (1) is truthy ✓\n   - `'padding'` is in `ALLOWED_CSS_PROPERTIES` ✓\n   - `'var(--mantine-spacing-lg)'` passes `CSS_VALUE_UNSAFE` test (no `{}<>;`) ✓\n4. `elementMap[1]` → the Card `<div>` DOM reference ✓\n5. **Strategy dispatch:**\n   - `origin.origin` → `'mantine-prop'`\n   - `overrideStrategies['mantine-prop']` → `mantineStrategy`\n6. **Check for existing override:** `overrideRecords['1:padding']` → undefined (first override)\n7. **`mantineStrategy.apply()` executes:**\n   - `buildSelector(1)`:\n     - `elementMap[1]` → the Card element\n     - `el.getAttribute('data-testid')` → `'dashboard-card'`\n     - Returns `'[data-testid=\"dashboard-card\"]'`\n   - Adds to `overrideRules`:\n     ```javascript\n     overrideRules['[data-testid=\"dashboard-card\"]'] = { padding: 'var(--mantine-spacing-lg)' }\n     ```\n   - Calls `updateOverrideSheet()`:\n     - `buildOverrideCSS(overrideRules)` →\n       `'[data-testid=\"dashboard-card\"] { padding: var(--mantine-spacing-lg) !important; }'`\n     - No existing `<style>` element → creates one:\n       ```html\n       <style id=\"__zerofog_overrides__\" data-zerofog-ui=\"true\">\n       [data-testid=\"dashboard-card\"] { padding: var(--mantine-spacing-lg) !important; }\n       </style>\n       ```\n     - Appends to `document.head`\n   - Returns `OverrideRecord`:\n     ```javascript\n     {\n       strategy: 'mantine-var',\n       originType: 'mantine-prop',\n       selId: 1,\n       selector: '[data-testid=\"dashboard-card\"]',\n       cssProperty: 'padding',\n       cssValue: 'var(--mantine-spacing-lg)',\n       component: 'Card',\n       prop: 'p'\n     }\n     ```\n8. Stores in `overrideRecords['1:padding']`\n\n**CSS rendering chain:**\n\n```\nBrowser CSS engine sees:\n  1. Mantine's original style: .mantine-Card-root { padding: var(--mantine-spacing-md) }\n  2. Our override: [data-testid=\"dashboard-card\"] { padding: var(--mantine-spacing-lg) !important }\n\n  → !important wins → padding resolves to var(--mantine-spacing-lg)\n  → Mantine CSS variable: --mantine-spacing-lg = 20px (from :root)\n  → Computed: padding: 20px (was 16px)\n```\n\n**What user sees:** The Card's padding visually increases from 16px to 20px. The change is instant (one frame). The green selection overlay may no longer perfectly match the element's new bounds (it was positioned at click time).\n\n**DOM after preview:**\n\n```html\n<!-- In <head>: -->\n<style id=\"__zerofog_overrides__\" data-zerofog-ui=\"true\">\n[data-testid=\"dashboard-card\"] { padding: var(--mantine-spacing-lg) !important; }\n</style>\n```\n\n**Memory after preview:**\n\n```javascript\noverrideRules = {\n  '[data-testid=\"dashboard-card\"]': {\n    padding: 'var(--mantine-spacing-lg)'\n  }\n}\noverrideRecords = {\n  '1:padding': {\n    strategy: 'mantine-var',\n    originType: 'mantine-prop',\n    selId: 1,\n    selector: '[data-testid=\"dashboard-card\"]',\n    cssProperty: 'padding',\n    cssValue: 'var(--mantine-spacing-lg)',\n    component: 'Card',\n    prop: 'p'\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Phase 8b: Tailwind Token Hover (Alternative Path)\n\nIf the element's padding origin was `tailwind` with `className: 'p-4'`:\n\n**Panel sends:**\n```javascript\n{\n  cssProperty: 'padding',\n  cssValue: 'p-8',       // The new Tailwind class — not a CSS value!\n  origin: { origin: 'tailwind', className: 'p-4' }\n}\n```\n\n**`tailwindStrategy.apply()` executes:**\n\n1. `oldClass = origin.className` → `'p-4'`\n2. `newClass = cssValue` → `'p-8'`\n3. `el.classList.contains('p-4')` → true → `el.classList.remove('p-4')`\n4. `el.classList.add('p-8')`\n5. Creates `MutationObserver`:\n   ```javascript\n   observer.observe(el, { attributes: true, attributeFilter: ['class'] })\n   ```\n6. Returns record with `{ oldClass: 'p-4', newClass: 'p-8', observer }`\n\n**DOM change:** Element's class attribute: `\"p-4 flex gap-2 ...\"` → `\"flex gap-2 ... p-8\"`\n\n**What user sees:** Same visual result — padding increases. But DevTools shows class change, not a `<style>` tag. No `<style id=\"__zerofog_overrides__\">` created (Tailwind overrides don't use it).\n\n---\n\n### Phase 9: Token Mouseout — Revert Preview\n\n**User action:** Moves mouse away from the \"lg\" button without clicking.\n\n**Panel processing:**\n\n1. Token button's `onmouseout` fires\n2. Checks: is this token in `pendingChanges`? No (user didn't click) → revert\n3. Panel sends `zerofog:revert` postMessage:\n   ```javascript\n   {\n     type: 'zerofog:revert',\n     sessionId: '...',\n     version: 1,\n     payload: { selectionId: 1, cssProperty: 'padding' }\n   }\n   ```\n\n**Inspector processing:**\n\n1. `messageHandlers['zerofog:revert']` fires\n2. Calls `removeOverride(1, 'padding')`\n3. Looks up `overrideRecords['1:padding']` → found\n4. Gets strategy: `overrideStrategies['mantine-prop']` → `mantineStrategy`\n5. Calls `mantineStrategy.remove(el, record)`:\n   - Deletes `overrideRules['[data-testid=\"dashboard-card\"]'].padding`\n   - Selector has no remaining props → deletes entire selector entry\n   - `updateOverrideSheet()`:\n     - `buildOverrideCSS({})` → empty string\n     - `<style>` element exists but CSS is empty → `styleEl.remove()` (removes from DOM)\n6. Deletes `overrideRecords['1:padding']`\n\n**For Tailwind revert:**\n\n1. `tailwindStrategy.remove(el, record)`:\n   - `record.observer.disconnect()` — stops watching for class changes\n   - `el.classList.remove('p-8')` — removes the new class\n   - `el.classList.add('p-4')` — restores the original class\n\n**What user sees:** Element snaps back to original padding (16px). Instantaneous.\n\n**Memory after revert:**\n\n```javascript\noverrideRules = {}         // empty again\noverrideRecords = {}       // empty again\n// DOM: <style> tag removed\n```\n\n---\n\n### Phase 10: Token Click — Commit Pending Change\n\n**User action:** Clicks the \"lg\" button in the Padding row.\n\n**Panel processing:**\n\n1. Token button's `onclick` fires\n2. Calls internal `selectToken('padding', 'lg', '16px')`:\n   - Resolves `lg` → pixel value via token map lookup\n   - Calls `detectStyleOrigin` result from selection (already cached)\n   - Stores pending change:\n     ```javascript\n     pendingChanges['padding'] = {\n       property: 'padding',\n       token: 'lg',\n       previousToken: 'md',\n       previousCssValue: '16px',\n       cssProperty: 'padding',\n       cssValue: 'var(--mantine-spacing-lg)',\n       styleOrigin: { origin: 'mantine-prop', prop: 'p', value: 'md', component: 'Card' }\n     }\n     ```\n3. Sends `zerofog:preview` (same as hover — applies the override)\n4. Refreshes toolbar UI (button turns blue)\n\n**Panel UI after click:**\n\n```\nPadding    ▸ mantine\n[xs][sm][md][■lg][xl]\n            ^^^^ BLUE background, white text\n```\n\n- `●md` loses its active highlight (was the current value, now superseded)\n- `■lg` gets blue background (#3b82f6) = pending change\n\n**Key difference from hover:** The override PERSISTS when mouse leaves the button. On mouseout, the panel checks `pendingChanges['padding']` → exists with token `'lg'` → doesn't revert.\n\n---\n\n### Phase 11: Hover While Pending — Preview Without Losing Pending\n\n**User action:** Has \"lg\" pending for padding. Now hovers \"xl\".\n\n**Panel processing:**\n\n1. Mouseenter on \"xl\" button → sends `zerofog:revert` for padding (removes lg preview)\n2. Immediately sends `zerofog:preview` for padding with xl value\n3. Element shows xl padding (even larger)\n\n**On mouseout from \"xl\":**\n\n1. Panel checks: is \"xl\" in pendingChanges? No → revert xl\n2. Re-applies pending \"lg\":\n   - Sends `zerofog:preview` with lg value\n   - Element returns to lg padding\n\nThis is the `revertAndReapplyPending()` pattern from the toolbar code.\n\n---\n\n### Phase 12: Multiple Property Changes\n\n**User action:** Also clicks \"sm\" for Gap.\n\n**Panel adds second pending change:**\n\n```javascript\npendingChanges = {\n  padding: { token: 'lg', cssValue: 'var(--mantine-spacing-lg)', ... },\n  gap:     { token: 'sm', cssValue: 'var(--mantine-spacing-sm)', ... }\n}\n```\n\n**Inspector memory now has two overrides:**\n\n```javascript\noverrideRules = {\n  '[data-testid=\"dashboard-card\"]': {\n    padding: 'var(--mantine-spacing-lg)',\n    gap: 'var(--mantine-spacing-sm)'\n  }\n}\noverrideRecords = {\n  '1:padding': { strategy: 'mantine-var', ... },\n  '1:gap':     { strategy: 'mantine-var', ... }\n}\n```\n\n**DOM:**\n\n```html\n<style id=\"__zerofog_overrides__\" data-zerofog-ui=\"true\">\n[data-testid=\"dashboard-card\"] { padding: var(--mantine-spacing-lg) !important; gap: var(--mantine-spacing-sm) !important; }\n</style>\n```\n\n**Mixed-strategy example:** If padding was Mantine and border-radius was Tailwind:\n\n```javascript\noverrideRules = {\n  '[data-testid=\"dashboard-card\"]': {\n    padding: 'var(--mantine-spacing-lg)'\n    // Note: NO border-radius here — Tailwind doesn't use the style sheet\n  }\n}\noverrideRecords = {\n  '1:padding':       { strategy: 'mantine-var', selector: '...', ... },\n  '1:border-radius': { strategy: 'tailwind-class', oldClass: 'rounded-md', newClass: 'rounded-xl', observer: MutationObserver }\n}\n```\n\nDOM has both:\n- `<style>` tag with padding override\n- Element's classList: `rounded-md` removed, `rounded-xl` added\n- MutationObserver watching element's `class` attribute\n\n---\n\n### Phase 13: Done — Finalize Changes\n\n**User action:** Clicks \"Done\" button in panel.\n\n**Panel processing:**\n\n1. Collects all pending changes into an array:\n   ```javascript\n   var changeList = [\n     { property: 'padding', token: 'lg', previousToken: 'md', cssValue: 'var(--mantine-spacing-lg)', styleOrigin: {...} },\n     { property: 'gap', token: 'sm', previousToken: 'xs', cssValue: 'var(--mantine-spacing-sm)', styleOrigin: {...} }\n   ];\n   ```\n\n2. Calls `finalizeDiff(selection, changeList)`:\n   ```javascript\n   {\n     elementSelector: '[data-testid=\"dashboard-card\"]',\n     componentChain: ['Card', 'DashboardPage', 'AppShell'],\n     elementType: 'container',\n     changes: [\n       {\n         property: 'padding', token: 'lg', previousToken: 'md',\n         cssValue: 'var(--mantine-spacing-lg)',\n         styleOrigin: { origin: 'mantine-prop', prop: 'p', value: 'md', component: 'Card' }\n       },\n       {\n         property: 'gap', token: 'sm', previousToken: 'xs',\n         cssValue: 'var(--mantine-spacing-sm)',\n         styleOrigin: { origin: 'mantine-prop', prop: 'gap', value: 8, component: 'Card' }\n       }\n     ],\n     timestamp: '2026-03-01T18:45:23.456Z'\n   }\n   ```\n\n3. **Overrides REMAIN APPLIED.** The `<style>` tag stays. Tailwind class swaps stay. MutationObservers keep running. The preview persists until source code is edited and HMR replaces the component.\n\n4. Panel UI resets:\n   - Token toolbar hides\n   - `pendingChanges = {}`\n   - Panel shows summary of accumulated diffs\n\n**What user sees:** Token toolbar disappears. The card still shows the overridden padding/gap. The panel shows a diff summary.\n\n**Why keep overrides applied?** The three-phase commit model (from implementation plan): overrides are cleared only after the source edit is verified via HMR. If the source edit fails, the preview remains as a visual reference.\n\n---\n\n### Phase 14: Select Different Element\n\n**User action:** Clicks on a different element (e.g., a `<Button>`).\n\n**What happens:**\n\n1. New `handleClick` fires for the Button element\n2. Green overlay moves to the Button's bounds\n3. New `selectionId` (2) assigned\n4. `elementMap[2] = <button>` stored\n5. New selection object built + posted to panel\n6. **Previous overrides on Card (selId: 1) PERSIST:**\n   - `overrideRecords['1:padding']` and `'1:gap'` still exist\n   - `<style>` tag still applies to `[data-testid=\"dashboard-card\"]`\n   - Card still renders with lg padding + sm gap\n7. Panel shows token buttons for Button's editable categories:\n   - Button is `'interactive'` → categories: `['padding', 'border-radius']`\n\n**Memory:**\n\n```javascript\nselectionId = 2\nelementMap = { 1: <div.Card>, 2: <button.Button> }\nwindow.__ZEROFOG__.selected = { id: 2, ... }  // new selection\n\n// Old overrides still active:\noverrideRecords = {\n  '1:padding': { strategy: 'mantine-var', ... },\n  '1:gap':     { strategy: 'mantine-var', ... }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Phase 15: Deactivate — Escape Key\n\n**User action:** Presses Escape key.\n\n**Event chain:**\n\n1. `keydown` (capture) → `handleKeyDown(e)`\n2. `e.key === 'Escape'` → calls `deactivate()`\n\n**`deactivate()` execution:**\n\n```javascript\n// 1. Set flags\nactive = false;\nselectMode = false;\n\n// 2. Clear element references (allow GC)\nvar mapKeys = Object.keys(elementMap);  // ['1', '2']\nfor (var i = 0; i < mapKeys.length; i++) {\n  delete elementMap[mapKeys[i]];\n}\n// elementMap is now empty (same object reference, keys deleted)\n\n// 3. Clear hover state\nlastHoverTarget = null;\nhoverRafPending = false;\n\n// 4. Clean up ALL overrides via strategy dispatch (NEW in this spec)\nvar recordKeys = Object.keys(overrideRecords);  // ['1:padding', '1:gap']\nfor (var i = 0; i < recordKeys.length; i++) {\n  var record = overrideRecords[recordKeys[i]];\n  var el = elementMap[record.selId];  // Note: elementMap already cleared!\n  // el is undefined — strategy.remove must handle null element gracefully\n  var strategy = overrideStrategies[record.originType] || cssImportantStrategy;\n  if (el) strategy.remove(el, record);\n  delete overrideRecords[recordKeys[i]];\n}\n// IMPORTANT: For Mantine/CSS-fallback, remove() modifies overrideRules\n// For Tailwind, remove() disconnects observer — but el is null (already cleared)\n\n// 5. Clean up override sheet (belt-and-suspenders)\nvar overrideSheet = document.getElementById('__zerofog_overrides__');\nif (overrideSheet) overrideSheet.remove();\nvar ruleKeys = Object.keys(overrideRules);\nfor (var ri = 0; ri < ruleKeys.length; ri++) {\n  delete overrideRules[ruleKeys[ri]];\n}\n\n// 6. Reset global namespace\nwindow.__ZEROFOG__.inspectorActive = false;\nwindow.__ZEROFOG__.selectMode = false;\nwindow.__ZEROFOG__.selected = null;\n\n// 7. Hide overlays\noverlay.style.display = 'none';\nselectedOverlay.style.display = 'none';\nlabelEl.style.display = 'none';\n\n// 8. Remove all event listeners\ndocument.removeEventListener('mouseover', handleHover, true);\ndocument.removeEventListener('pointerdown', handlePointerDown, true);\ndocument.removeEventListener('click', handleClick, true);\ndocument.removeEventListener('keydown', handleKeyDown, true);\nwindow.removeEventListener('message', handleMessage);\n\n// 9. Notify parent\ndocument.dispatchEvent(new CustomEvent('zerofog:deselected'));\npostToParent('zerofog:deselected', null);\n```\n\n**NOTE: Ordering bug in deactivate():** `elementMap` is cleared in step 2, but `overrideRecords` cleanup in step 4 needs `elementMap[record.selId]` to find elements for Tailwind observer disconnect. Fix: clean up overrides BEFORE clearing elementMap. (This is a pre-existing issue that this spec's strategy pattern makes visible.)\n\n**DOM after deactivate:**\n\n- `<style id=\"__zerofog_overrides__\">` removed from `<head>`\n- All three overlays: `display:none`\n- Element's Tailwind classes: restored to original (if observer could access element)\n- Event listeners removed — mouseover/click/etc. no longer intercepted\n\n**Memory after deactivate:**\n\n```javascript\nactive = false\nselectMode = false\nselectionId = 2              // not reset — monotonically increasing\nelementMap = {}              // empty\noverrideRules = {}           // empty\noverrideRecords = {}         // empty\nlastHoverTarget = null\n\nwindow.__ZEROFOG__ = {\n  activateInspector: fn,     // still available for re-activation\n  deactivateInspector: fn,\n  selected: null,\n  inspectorActive: false,\n  selectMode: false,\n  elementMap: {}\n}\n```\n\n**What