            "new_string": "3. This is correct behavior — it matches what would happen if the source had `p-8`\n\n---\n\n## Architecture Review Findings (2026-03-02)\n\n**Review team:** frontend, security, design, mts (Master Technical Strategist), performance\n**Selection rationale:** Section 14's 20-phase UX flow is DOM/CSS-heavy (frontend), relies on cross-frame postMessage (security), defines the entire user interaction model (design), involves intricate state management and edge cases (mts), and has hot-path operations like hover/scroll (performance).\n**Mode:** both (clink + native — 10 total reviewers)\n\n---\n\n### Cross-Reviewer Consensus\n\nIssues flagged independently by 3+ reviewers — highest-confidence signals:\n\n| # | Issue | Flagged By | Severity |\n|---|-------|-----------|----------|\n| 1 | **`deactivate()` ordering bug**: `elementMap.clear()` runs before `overrideRecords` cleanup, so Tailwind MutationObservers never disconnect — memory leak and ghost observers | ALL 10 reviewers | CRITICAL |\n| 2 | **Tailwind JIT class non-existence**: Swapping to a class not in the original build (e.g., `p-8` when only `p-4` was used) silently fails — the class has no corresponding CSS rule in the JIT-generated stylesheet | frontend (×2), mts (×2), performance, design | CRITICAL |\n| 3 | **Selection overlay doesn't track scroll**: Green overlay positioned at click-time viewport coordinates becomes visually misaligned after scroll. No scroll/resize handler exists. | frontend (×2), design (×2), mts, performance | HIGH |\n| 4 | **React 19 breaks `detectStyleOrigin` for Mantine**: `_debugOwner` removed in React 19; the fiber traversal in `walkComponentChain` that identifies Mantine props will silently return empty results, making all Mantine elements fall to CSS `!important` path | frontend (×2), mts (×2) | CRITICAL |\n| 5 | **MutationObserver cascade with multiple Tailwind overrides**: Each Tailwind override on the same element adds a new observer. Multiple observers