          "text": "Implement the following plan:\n\n# Phase 4a Post-Review Remediation: 5 Architecture Findings\n\n**Linear:** ZF0-848 | **Branch:** `fix/phase3-post-remediation-fixes`\n\n## Context\n\nPhase 4a (port pure functions, override engine, Tailwind regex fix) was implemented and passed all tests. A 10-reviewer architecture review (5 clink + 5 native) identified 5 high-confidence findings that need remediation before merge. This plan addresses all 5 in priority order.\n\n## Files to Modify\n\n| File | Findings | Changes |\n|------|----------|---------|\n| `src/client/inspector.js` | F1, F4 | `buildSelector` fallback + CSS injection validation in `applyOverride` |\n| `src/client/toolbar.js` | F2, F3, F5 | React 19 dual-strategy + Tailwind regex + sentinel try/catch/finally |\n| `tests/client/inspector.test.ts` | F1, F4 | 7 new tests |\n| `tests/client/toolbar.test.ts` | F2, F3, F5 | 10 new tests |\n\n## Step 1: F5 — `buildTokenMaps` sentinel leak (HIGH)\n\n**File:** `src/client/toolbar.js` lines 38-63\n\n**Problem:** If `_getStyle(sentinel)` throws, the sentinel `<div>` stays in the DOM permanently.\n\n**Change:** Wrap the resolution loop in `try/catch/finally`:\n\n```js\ndocument.body.appendChild(sentinel);\n\ntry {\n  for (var i = 0; i < TOOLBAR_SIZES.length; i++) {\n    // ... existing resolution loop unchanged ...\n  }\n} catch (_e) {\n  return { spacing: {}, radius: {} };   // graceful degradation\n} finally {\n  sentinel.remove();                     // always cleans up\n}\n\nradiusMap['0px'] = 'none';\nreturn { spacing: spacingMap, radius: radiusMap };\n```\n\nUses `sentinel.remove()` (already used elsewhere in codebase) instead of `document.body.removeChild(sentinel)`. Catch returns empty maps for graceful degradation — partial token maps would produce inconsistent UI.\n\n**Tests (2):**\n- Sentinel removed even when styleGetter throws\n- Returns empty maps on error\n\n## Step 2: F4 — CSS injection in `applyOverride` (HIGH)\n\n**File:** `src/client/inspector.js` lines 521-558\n\n**Problem:** `cssProperty` and `cssValue` pass directly to `buildOverrideCSS` with no validation. Malicious payloads like `cssValue: \"red; } body { display:none\"` could inject arbitrary CSS.\n\n**Change:** Add allowlist + value sanitization inside the IIFE, before `buildSelector`:\n\n```js\nvar ALLOWED_CSS_PROPERTIES = [\n  'padding', 'padding-top', 'padding-right', 'padding-bottom', 'padding-left',\n  'margin', 'margin-top', 'margin-right', 'margin-bottom', 'margin-left',\n  'gap', 'row-gap', 'column-gap',\n  'border-radius', 'border-top-left-radius', 'border-top-right-radius',\n  'border-bottom-left-radius', 'border-bottom-right-radius',\n  'color', 'background-color', 'background',\n  'font-size', 'font-weight', 'font-family',\n  'display'\n];\n\nvar CSS_VALUE_UNSAFE = /[{}<>;]/;\n```\n\nThen modify `applyOverride` to validate early:\n\n```js\nfunction applyOverride(selId, cssProperty, cssValue) {\n  if (!selId) return;\n  if (ALLOWED_CSS_PROPERTIES.indexOf(cssProperty) === -1) return;\n  if (CSS_VALUE_UNSAFE.test(cssValue)) return;\n  // ... rest unchanged\n}\n```\n\nAllowlist covers exactly what the toolbar UI can set (spacing, radius, color, font, display). `indexOf` for ES5 compat. Silent return — CSS injection is not user-facing.\n\n**Tests (4):**\n- Allowed property `padding` is accepted\n- Disallowed property `position` is rejected (no override sheet created)\n- Value with `}` is rejected\n- Value with `;` is rejected\n\n## Step 3: F1 — `buildSelector` null return (CRITICAL)\n\n**File:** `src/client/inspector.js` lines 526-534\n\n**Problem:** Elements without `data-testid` or `data-cortex-id` cause `buildSelector` to return `null`, silently dropping overrides. User clicks preview, nothing happens.\n\n**Change:** Replace final `return null` with auto-assignment fallback:\n\n```js\nfunction buildSelector(selId) {\n  var el = elementMap[selId];\n  if (!el) return null;\n  var testId = el.getAttribute ? el.getAttribute('data-testid') : null;\n  if (testId) return '[data-testid=\"' + testId + '\"]';\n  var cortexId = el.getAttribute ? el.getAttribute('data-cortex-id') : null;\n  if (cortexId) return '[data-cortex-id=\"' + cortexId + '\"]';\n  // Fallback: assign stable cortex-id so override has a target selector\n  var generatedId = 'zerofog-' + selId;\n  if (el.setAttribute) {\n    el.setAttribute('data-cortex-id', generatedId);\n    console.warn(\n      '[zerofog] Element lacks data-testid; auto-assigned data-cortex-id=\"' +\n        generatedId + '\". Add a data-testid for stable selectors.'\n    );\n  }\n  return '[data-cortex-id=\"' + generatedId + '\"]';\n}\n```\n\n`zerofog-<selId>` is stable (selectionId is monotonic per session). `console.warn` nudges developers to add proper test IDs.\n\n**Tests (3):**\n- Element without any ID gets auto-assigned `data-cortex-id` and override works\n- `console.warn` is logged with `[zerofog]` prefix\n- Multiple fallback elements get unique selectors\n\n## Step 4: F3 — Tailwind regex gaps (HIGH)\n\n**File:** `src/client/toolbar.js` lines 164-170\n\n**Problem:** Current regex misses stacked modifiers (`sm:hover:p-4`), negative margins (`-m-4`), arbitrary values (`p-[16px]`), and hyphenated modifiers (`group-hover:p-4`).\n\n**Change:** Three targeted regex fixes:\n\n```js\nvar twPatterns = {\n  padding: /(?:^|\\s)(?:[\\w-]+:)*p[xytblr]?-(\\d+(?:\\.5)?|px|auto|\\[\\S+?\\])/,\n  margin:  /(?:^|\\s)(?:[\\w-]+:)*-?m[xytblr]?-(\\d+(?:\\.5)?|px|auto|\\[\\S+?\\])/,\n  gap:     /(?:^|\\s)(?:[\\w-]+:)*gap-(\\d+(?:\\.5)?|px|auto|\\[\\S+?\\])/,\n  'border-radius': /(?:^|\\s)(?:[\\w-]+:)*rounded(?:-(none|sm|md|lg|xl|2xl|3xl|full|\\[\\S+?\\]))?/,\n};\n```\n\n| Change | Why |\n|--------|-----|\n| `(?:[\\w]+:)?` → `(?:[\\w-]+:)*` | `*` handles stacked modifiers; `[\\w-]` handles `group-hover:` |\n| Added `-?` before `m[xytblr]?` | Captures negative margins; only on margin (padding/gap/radius can't be negative) |\n| Added `\\[\\S+?\\]` alternative | Captures Tailwind v3 arbitrary bracket values |\n\nVerified `prose-lg` still rejected: regex matches `p` + `r` (from `[xytblr]`) + expects `-` but gets `o` → no match.\n\n**Tests (5):**\n- Stacked modifiers `sm:hover:p-4` matches\n- Negative margin `-m-4` matches\n- Arbitrary bracket value `p-[16px]` matches\n- Hyphenated modifier `group-hover:p-4` matches\n- `prose-lg` still rejected (regression)\n\n## Step 5: F2 — React 19 breaks `detectStyleOrigin` (CRITICAL)\n\n**File:** `src/client/toolbar.js` lines 102-153\n\n**Problem:** Function walks `_debugOwner` chain unconditionally. React 19 removes `_debugOwner` and uses `fiber.return` — all elements return `{ origin: 'unknown' }`.\n\n**Change:** Port the dual-strategy pattern from `walkComponentChain` (inspector.js:50-83):\n\n```js\nif (fiberKeys.length > 0) {\n  var domFiber = element[fiberKeys[0]];\n  var useDebugOwner = domFiber &&\n    Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty.call(domFiber, '_debugOwner');\n\n  var owner = null;\n  if (useDebugOwner) {\n    owner = domFiber ? domFiber._debugOwner : null;\n  } else {\n    owner = domFiber ? domFiber.return : null;\n  }\n\n  var depth = 0;\n  var MAX_DEPTH = 20;\n\n  while (owner && depth < MAX_DEPTH) {\n    // React 19: skip non-component fibers (HostComponent=5, HostRoot=3, etc.)\n    if (!useDebugOwner && owner.tag !== 0 && owner.tag !== 1) {\n      owner = owner.return;\n      depth++;\n      continue;\n    }\n\n    // ... existing propMap + themeDefaults checks unchanged ...\n\n    owner = useDebugOwner ? owner._debugOwner : owner.return;\n    depth++;\n  }\n}\n```\n\nKey: `hasOwnProperty.call` detects React 18 (where `_debugOwner` exists even if `null`). React 19 fallback uses `fiber.return` with tag filtering (0=Function, 1=Class). Depth counter increments on skipped fibers to prevent infinite loops.\n\n**Tests (3):**\n- React 19 fiber (no `_debugOwner`, has `return`+`tag`) → detects mantine-prop\n- React 18 fiber (has `_debugOwner`) → still works (regression)\n- React 19 skips HostComponent (tag 5) to reach component fiber\n\n## Implementation Order\n\nSequenced for independent, testable commits:\n\n| Order | Finding | Severity | File(s) | Tests |\n|-------|---------|----------|---------|-------|\n| 1 | F5 sentinel leak | HIGH | toolbar.js | 2 |\n| 2 | F4 CSS injection | HIGH | inspector.js | 4 |\n| 3 | F1 null selector | CRITICAL | inspector.js | 3 |\n| 4 | F3 regex gaps | HIGH | toolbar.js | 5 |\n| 5 | F2 React 19 | CRITICAL | toolbar.js | 3 |\n\n**Total:** ~50 lines of source changes, 17 new tests\n\n## Verification\n\n```bash\ncd visual-editor\nnpm run build          # Both client scripts compile\nnpm test               # All existing + 17 new tests pass\nnpm run typecheck      # No type errors\n```\n\n\nIf you need specific details from before exiting plan mode (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /Users/derricklee/.claude/projects/-Users-derricklee-cortex/f6f702b7-5f1e-4c3a-8375-9ca8c381d14a.jsonl\n\nIf this plan can be broken down into multiple independent tasks, consider using the TeamCreate tool to create a team and parallelize the work.",
