          "text": "`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`\n**The `createMockFiber` factory subtlety**: The original factory always sets `_debugOwner: null` on every fiber. This matters now because `walkComponentChain` uses `'_debugOwner' in fiber` (property existence). If we keep `_debugOwner` in the factory defaults, all mock fibers default to Strategy A (React 18). For React 19 tests (Strategy B), we'll use plain objects without `_debugOwner` property — this forces the `in` check to fail and Strategy B kicks in.\n\n**Portal detection flow in `resolveSource`**: The `ownTestId` vs `testId` distinction is critical. If the element _itself_ has `data-testid`, no ancestry check needed. But if testId came from `closest()` (a DOM ancestor), we verify the DOM ancestor is also a fiber ancestor via `isFiberAncestor`. If not → React portal → discard the testId.\n`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`\n\nNow writing the comprehensive test file.",
