— tags can shift between versions. React 19 also replaced `_debugOwner` with `_debugStack`. The `fiber.return` walk includes HostComponent, Suspense, Context providers, producing noisier chains than `_debugOwner`.\n\n**Fix:** Check `typeof fiber.type === 'function'` instead of magic tag numbers. Investigate `_debugStack` for React 19.\n\n#### H2. `'_debugOwner' in fiber` walks prototype chain + undocumented prod behavior\n\n**Flagged by:** jsts (F5), mts (C2)\n\nThe `in` operator checks prototypes. If anything pollutes `Object.prototype._debugOwner`, all fibers route to Strategy A. Additionally, React 18 prod builds strip `_debugOwner` — the \"React 18\" strategy only activates in dev mode. This is accidentally correct (Strategy B works for prod) but the comments don't explain it.\n\n**Fix:** Use `Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty.call(fiber, '_debugOwner')`. Update comments to document dev-only behavior.\n\n#### H3. `isServerComponent` is semantically wrong\n\n**Flagged by:** frontend (H5), jsts (F9), mts (M1)\n\n\"No fiber found\" ≠ \"server component.\" Plain HTML, Vue/Svelte elements, and React 18 prod elements all trigger `isServerComponent: true`.\n\n**Fix:** Rename to `hasClientFiber: boolean` or use tri-state `'client' | 'server' | 'unknown'`.\n\n#### H4. Selection payload missing data for Phase 4a/4b\n\n**Flagged by:** mts (H2)\n\nNo `data-cortex-id` for CSS selector targeting. No CSS custom property resolution (only 10 hardcoded resolved values). No parent context (flex/grid for gap editing). Stale `bounds` snapshot.\n\n**Fix:** Design a `inspector:query-element` request/response message type for on-demand data fetching. Add `cortexId` to selection payload.\n\n#### H5. `handleMessage` not extensible for downstream phases\n\n**Flagged by:** mts (H3)\n\nSimple if/else for 2 message types. Phases 4a/4b/5 need 6+ additional types. Will become unwieldy switch statement.\n\n**Fix:** Replace with dispatch table pattern:\n```javascript\nvar messageHandlers = {};\nmessageHandlers['inspector:enter-select'] = function() { ... };\n```\n\n#### H6. No throttling on hover — `resolveSource` on every mouseover\n\n**Flagged by:** frontend (H1)\n\nEach hover: `Object.keys()` on DOM element, fiber tree walk, `closest()` DOM walk, double `getBoundingClientRect()`. No caching, no rAF throttle.\n\n**Fix:** Cache last hover target, cache fiber keys in WeakMap, wrap in `requestAnimationFrame`.\n\n#### H7. `.d.ts` is manually maintained — types unchecked against implementation\n\n**Flagged by:** jsts (Critical 1)\n\n`tsconfig.json` doesn't include `.js` files. The `.d.ts` sidecar is a \"type promise\" with no compiler validation. Signatures can drift silently.\n\n**Fix:** Convert `inspector.js` → `inspector.ts`. tsup handles the IIFE bundling identically for `.ts` input. Eliminates the `.d.ts` file entirely. (Medium effort but eliminates 5+ findings.)\n\n#### H8. Depth cap tests use `toBeLessThanOrEqual(20)` instead of exact assertion\n\n**Flagged by:** testing (High 2)\n\nTests at lines 198, 345, 356 use `<=` which would still pass if the cap were off-by-one or changed to 200. Don't verify which components are in the truncated chain.\n\n**Fix:** Change to `toBe(20)`. Assert first/last elements of truncated chain.\n\n#### H9. WS Origin header is optional — CSWSH possible\n\n**Flagged by:** security (Finding 1)\n\nServer accepts WebSocket upgrades without Origin header (`if (origin && ...)`). Modern browsers always send Origin, but non-browser clients bypass the check.\n\n**Fix:** Require Origin: `if (!origin || !isLoopbackOrigin(origin))`.\n\n---\n\n### MEDIUM\n\n| Finding | Reviewer | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `classifyElement` Mantine-only | frontend, mts | Hardcoded component names; extract to configurable map |\n| `getComponentName` missing tests | testing, jsts | No dedicated tests; edge cases (string type, empty displayName) uncovered |\n| `findReactFiberKeys` missing tests | testing | No direct tests; concurrent root multi-key case