            "new_string": "All 5 reviews were conducted by Claude Task agents running in parallel with direct codebase access. Each agent independently read the implementation, test suite, build config, and server code. Findings were consolidated by deduplication, cross-referencing severity assessments, and validating critical claims against the actual code. The template variable mismatch (CR1) was independently verified by reading both `inspector.js` source, tsup-bundled dist output, and server replacement code.\n\n---\n---\n\n# Phase 3: Post-Remediation Review (2026-02-27)\n\nReview team: **frontend**, **security**, **jsts**, **testing**, **mts** (same panel)\nMode: native (5 Claude Task agents)\nScope: 8 fixes applied to `inspector.js`, `inspector.d.ts`, `inspector.test.ts` addressing CR1, CR2, H2, H3, H5, H6, H8 + 10 new tests\n\n---\n\n## Original Finding Resolution Status\n\n| Original | Severity | Status | Notes |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| CR1 — Template variable mismatch | CRITICAL | **RESOLVED** | `__SESSION_ID__`/`__SIDECAR_ORIGIN__` matches server regex. Verified in dist output. |\n| CR2 — elementMap unbounded leak | CRITICAL | **RESOLVED** (with caveats) | Cap 50 + eviction + clear on deactivate. See PR-H1 for plain-object concerns. |\n| CR3 — Browser IIFE zero coverage | CRITICAL | **NOT ADDRESSED** | All 10 new tests are pure-function unit tests. IIFE runtime still untested. |\n| H2 — `in` operator prototype chain | HIGH | **RESOLVED** | `hasOwnProperty.call()` is correct and robust. |\n| H3 — isServerComponent naming | HIGH | **RESOLVED** | Clean rename to `hasClientFiber` across all 3 files. Zero stale references. |\n| H5 — handleMessage not extensible | HIGH | **RESOLVED** (with caveat) | Dispatch table correct. See PR-H2 for prototype pollution. |\n| H6 — No hover throttling | HIGH | **RESOLVED** (with caveat) | rAF + target cache correct. See PR-M1 for detached-element edge case. |\n| H8 — Depth cap test assertions | HIGH | **RESOLVED** | `toBe(20)` +