 = false`\n\n#### elementMap + Eviction (~2 tests)\n- Selection adds entry to `window.__ZEROFOG__.elementMap`\n- After 51 clicks, elementMap has exactly 50 entries (oldest evicted)\n\n#### Message Validation (~1-2 tests)\n- `isValidInbound` rejects wrong origin (message from different origin ignored)\n- `isValidInbound` rejects missing sessionId\n\n**Human collaboration opportunity**: The `isValidInbound` / `handleMessage` tests involve creating `MessageEvent` objects with specific `origin` and `data` properties. This is where the message validation logic is most nuanced — the student implements these 2-3 tests.\n\n### Step 3: Run tests + typecheck + build\n\n```bash\ncd visual-editor && npm test        # All ~115+ tests pass\ncd visual-editor && npm run typecheck  # Zero errors\ncd visual-editor && npm run build      # 13+ KB IIFE bundle\n```\n\nVerify dist output still has `__SESSION_ID__` / `__SIDECAR_ORIGIN__` in string literals.\n\n## Verification\n\n1. `npm test` — all tests pass (existing 103 + ~12-15 new IIFE integration tests)\n2. `npm run typecheck` — zero errors\n3. `npm run build` — dist/client/inspector.js produced\n4. Verify `Object.create(null)` appears in dist for both `messageHandlers` and `elementMap`\n\n## Risks & Mitigations\n\n| Risk | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|\n| happy-dom rAF timing differs from browser | happy-dom executes rAF synchronously — simpler than real browser, but tests still validate the callback logic |\n| `vi.resetModules()` module cache reset | Use separate `describe` block with `beforeEach` reset; existing pure-function tests unaffected |\n| `window.parent === window` in happy-dom | `postToParent()` is a no-op — acceptable; we're testing DOM/event behavior, not postMessage delivery |\n| `getBoundingClientRect()` returns zeros in happy-dom | This is actually what detached elements return too — the zero-rect guard handles both cases |\n| Payload isolation change (`e.data.payload`) | Current handlers ignore the argument entirely, so passing `undefined` (no payload on current messages) is safe. Future Phase 4 messages will include `payload`. |\n"
